msgid "Active"
msgstr "Attivo"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:255
msgid "Only **active** taxes can be added to new documents."
msgstr "Solo le imposte **attive** possono essere aggiunte a nuovi documenti."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:258
msgid ""
"It is not possible to delete taxes that have already been used. Instead, you "
"can deactivate them to prevent future use."
msgstr ""
"Non è possibile eliminare le imposte già utilizzate. È invece possibile "
"disattivarle per impedirne l'uso futuro."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:262
msgid ""
"This field can be modified from the :ref:`list view <taxes/list_activation>`."
msgstr ""
"Questo campo può essere modificato dalla :ref:`vista elenco <taxes/"
"list_activation>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:267
msgid "Tax type"
msgstr "Tipo di imposta"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:269
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Tax Type` determines the tax application, which also "
"restricts where it is displayed."
msgstr ""
"Il :guilabel:`Tipo di imposta` determina l'applicazione dell'imposta che ne "
"limita anche la visualizzazione."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:271
msgid "**Sales**: Customer invoices, product customer taxes, etc."
msgstr "**Vendite**: fatture cliente, imposte cliente prodotto, ecc."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:272
msgid "**Purchase**: Vendor bills, product vendor taxes, etc."
msgstr "**Acquisti**: fatture fornitore, imposte fornitore prodotto, ecc."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:273
msgid "**None**"
msgstr "**Nessuno**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:276
msgid ""
"You can use :guilabel:`None` for taxes that you want to include in "
"a :ref:`Group of Taxes <taxes/computation>` but that you do not want to list "
"along with other sales or purchase taxes."
msgstr ""
"Puoi utilizzare :guilabel:`Nessuno` per le imposte che vuoi includere in un "
":ref:`Gruppo di imposte <taxes/computation>` ma che non vuoi elencare con le "
"altre imposte per vendite e acquisti."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:282
msgid "Definition tab"
msgstr "Scheda Definizione"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:284
msgid ""
"Allocate with precision the amount of the taxable basis or percentages of "
"the computed tax to multiple accounts and tax grids."
msgstr ""
"Assegna con precisione l'importo della base imponibile o le percentuali "
"dell'imposta calcolata a più conti e griglie fiscali."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid "Allocate tax amounts to the right accounts and tax grids"
msgstr ""
"Assegnazione importi delle imposte ai conti e alle griglie fiscali corretti"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:290
msgid "**Based On**:"
msgstr "**Basata su**:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:292
msgid ":guilabel:`Base`: the price on the invoice line"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Base`: il prezzo sulla riga della fattura"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:293
msgid ":guilabel:`% of tax`: a percentage of the computed tax."
msgstr ":guilabel:`% imposta`: percentuale dell'imposta calcolata."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:295
msgid "**Account**: if defined, an additional journal item is recorded."
msgstr ""
"**Conto**: se indicato, viene registrato un movimento contabile aggiuntivo."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:296
msgid ""
"**Tax Grids**:  used to generate :doc:`tax reports <reporting/tax_returns>` "
"automatically, according to your country's regulations."
msgstr ""
"**Griglie imposte**:  usate per generare automaticamente :doc:`resoconti "
"fiscali <reporting/tax_returns>`, secondo la normativa del Paese."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:302
msgid "Advanced options tab"
msgstr "Scheda Opzioni avanzate"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:307
msgid "Label on invoices"
msgstr "Etichetta su fatture"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:309
msgid ""
"The tax label is displayed on each invoice line in the :guilabel:`Taxes` "
"column. This is visible to *front-end* users on exported invoices, in "
"customer portals, etc."
msgstr ""
"L'etichetta dell'imposta viene mostrata su ogni riga di fattura nella "
"colonna :guilabel:`Imposte`. È visibile agli utenti del *front-end* su "
"fatture esportate, nei portali clienti, ecc. "

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid "The label on invoices is displayed on each invoice line"
msgstr "L'etichetta delle fatture visualizzata su ogni riga della fattura"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:318
msgid "Tax group"
msgstr "Gruppo imposte"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:320
msgid ""
"Select which **tax group** the tax belongs to. The tax group name is the "
"displayed above the **total** line on exported invoices and in customer "
"portals."
msgstr ""
"Seleziona il **gruppo imposta** a cui appartiene l'imposta. Il nome del "
"gruppo viene visualizzato sopra la riga **totale** sulle fatture esportate e "
"nei portali dei clienti."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:323
msgid ""
"Tax groups include different iterations of the same tax. This can be useful "
"when you must record the same tax differently according to :doc:`fiscal "
"positions <taxes/fiscal_positions>`."
msgstr ""
"I gruppi imposte includono varie iterazioni della stessa imposta. Può essere "
"utile quando devi registrare la stessa imposta in modo diverso a seconda "
"delle :doc:`posizioni di bilancio <taxes/fiscal_positions>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid "The Tax Group name is different from the Label on Invoices"
msgstr "Il nome del gruppo fiscale è diverso dall'etichetta sulle fatture"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:331
msgid ""
"In the example above, the :guilabel:`0% EU S` tax for intra-community "
"customers in Europe records the amount on specific accounts and tax grids. "
"However, it remains a 0% tax to the customer. This is why the label "
"indicates :guilabel:`0% EU S`, and the tax group name above "
"the :guilabel:`Total` line indicates :guilabel:`VAT 0%`."
msgstr ""
"Nell'esempio precedente, l'imposta :guilabel:`0% EU S` per i clienti "
"intracomunitari in Europa registra l'importo su conti e griglie imposte "
"specifici. Tuttavia, per il cliente rimane un'imposta dello 0%. Per questo "
"motivo l'etichetta indica :guilabel:`0% EU S`, mentre il nome del gruppo "
"fiscale sopra la riga :guilabel:`Totale` indica :guilabel:`IVA 0%`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:337
msgid ""
"Taxes have three different labels, each one having a specific use. Refer to "
"the following table to see where they are displayed."
msgstr ""
"Le imposte hanno tre diverse etichette, ognuna delle quali ha un uso "
"specifico. Per vedere dove vengono visualizzate, consulta la tabella che "
"segue."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:341
msgid ":ref:`Tax Name <taxes/name>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Nome imposta <taxes/name>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:341
msgid ":ref:`Label on Invoice <taxes/label-invoices>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Etichetta su fattura <taxes/label-invoices>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:341
msgid ":ref:`Tax Group <taxes/tax-group>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Gruppo imposte <taxes/tax-group>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:344
msgid "Backend"
msgstr "Backend"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:344
msgid ":guilabel:`Taxes` column on exported invoices"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Imposte`, colonna su fatture esportate"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:344
msgid "Above the :guilabel:`Total` line on exported invoices"
msgstr "Sopra la riga :guilabel:`Totale` sulle fatture esportate "

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:352
msgid "Include in analytic cost"
msgstr "Includere nel costo analitico"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:354
msgid ""
"With this option activated, the tax amount is assigned to the same "
"**analytic account** as the invoice line."
msgstr ""
"Con questa opzione attivata, l'importo dell'imposta viene assegnato allo "
"stesso **conto analitico** della riga della fattura."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:360
msgid "Included in price"
msgstr "Includere nel prezzo"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:362
msgid ""
"With this option activated, the tax will treat the sales price on which it "
"is applied as a total including the tax amount. The tax computation will "
"split the sales price into a base amount and a tax amount. This makes it "
"suitable for B2C sales in most countries where prices are quoted tax-"
"inclusive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:367
msgid "`Total = Sales Price = Computed Tax-Excluded price + Tax`"
msgstr ""
"`Totale = Prezzo di vendita = Imposta calcolata-Prezzo escluso + Imposta`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:370
msgid ""
"A product has a sales price of $1000, and we apply a "
"10% :guilabel:`Percentage of Price` tax with :guilabel:`Included in Price`. "
"We then have:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:381
msgid ""
"For a guide on configuring tax-excluded and tax-included prices for B2B and "
"B2C customers, see :doc:`taxes/B2B_B2C`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:389
msgid "Affect base of subsequent taxes"
msgstr "Determinare imponibile imposte successive"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:391
msgid ""
"If this setting is enabled, any subsequent tax applied on the same product "
"line that has :ref:`taxes/base-affected` will be based on a modified sales "
"price. The exact behavior depends on whether the tax with :guilabel:`Affect "
"base of subsequent taxes` is :ref:`taxes/included-in-price` or not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:398
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Included in Price` is disabled, subsequent taxes "
"with :guilabel:`Base affected by preceding taxes` will be based on a "
"modified sales price equal to the original sales price plus the tax amount."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:403
msgid ""
"A product has a sales price of $1000, and we apply a "
"10% :guilabel:`Percentage of Price` tax with :guilabel:`Affect base of "
"subsequent taxes`. Any subsequent tax with :guilabel:`Base affected by "
"preceding taxes` will be based on a modified sales price of $1100."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:409
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Included in Price` is enabled, subsequent taxes "
"with :guilabel:`Base affected by preceding taxes` will be based on a "
"modified sales price equal to the original sales price minus the tax amount."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:414
msgid ""
"A product has a sales price of $1100, and we apply a "
"10% :guilabel:`Percentage of Price` tax with :guilabel:`Included in Price` "
"and :guilabel:`Affect base of subsequent taxes`. Any subsequent tax "
"with :guilabel:`Base affected by preceding taxes` will be based on a "
"modified sales price of $1000."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:419
msgid ""
"This setting is considered any time multiple taxes are applied to the same "
"product line, whether via a :ref:`group of taxes <taxes/computation>` or "
"multiple taxes added directly to a product line."
msgstr ""
"Questa impostazione è considerata ogni volta che più imposte vengono "
"applicate alla stessa riga di prodotto, sia tramite un :ref:`group of taxes "
"<taxes/computation>` sia tramite più imposte aggiunte direttamente a una "
"riga di prodotto."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid "The eco-tax is taken into the basis of the 21% VAT tax"
msgstr "La tassa ambientale viene presa come base per l'imposta IVA del 21%."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:426
msgid ""
"The order in which you add the taxes on a product line has no effect on how "
"amounts are computed. If you add taxes directly on a product line, only the "
"tax sequence determines the order in which they are applied."
msgstr ""
"L'ordine in cui si aggiungono le imposte a una riga di prodotto non ha alcun "
"effetto sul calcolo degli importi. Se si aggiungono le imposte direttamente "
"su una riga di prodotto, solo la sequenza delle imposte determina l'ordine "
"di applicazione."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:430
msgid ""
"To reorder the sequence, go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration "
"--> Taxes`, and drag and drop the lines with the handles next to the tax "
"names."
msgstr ""
"Per riordinare la sequenza, apri l'app :menuselection:`Contabilità --> "
"Configurazione --> Imposte` e trascina e rilascia le righe accanto ai nomi "
"delle imposte."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:0
msgid "The taxes' sequence in Odoo determines which tax is applied first"
msgstr ""
"La sequenza delle imposte in Odoo determina quale imposta viene applicata "
"per prima."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:439
msgid "Base affected by preceding taxes"
msgstr "Base affected by preceding taxes"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:441
msgid ""
"This setting, which is only visible in :doc:`developer mode <../../general/"
"developer_mode>`, determines whether any previous tax that :ref:`affects the "
"base of subsequent taxes <taxes/base-subsequent>` will modify the sales "
"price that this tax is based on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:446
msgid ""
"Taxes with :ref:`Included in Price <taxes/included-in-price>` always behave "
"as if this setting is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:450
msgid "Extra taxes"
msgstr "Imposte aggiuntive"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:452
msgid ""
"\"Extra taxes\" is a broad term referring to additional taxes beyond the "
"standard or basic taxes imposed by governments. These extra taxes can be "
"**luxury** taxes, **environmental** taxes, **import** or **export duties** "
"taxes, etc."
msgstr ""
"Con “Tasse aggiuntive” ci si riferisce a tasse extra rispetto a quelle "
"standard o di base imposte dai governi. Queste tasse aggiuntive possono "
"essere tasse di **lusso**, tasse **ambientali**, tasse di **importazione** o "
"**dazi di esportazione**, ecc."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:457
msgid ""
"The method to compute these taxes varies across different countries. We "
"recommend consulting your country's regulations to understand how to "
"calculate them for your business."
msgstr ""
"Il metodo di calcolo di queste imposte varia da Paese a Paese. Ti "
"consigliamo di consultare le normative del tuo Paese per capire come "
"calcolarle per la tua attività."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:460
msgid ""
"To compute an extra tax in Odoo, :ref:`create a tax <taxes/configuration>`, "
"enter a tax name, select a :ref:`Tax Computation <taxes/configuration>`, set "
"an :guilabel:`Amount`, and in the :guilabel:`Advanced Options` tab, "
"enable :guilabel:`Affect Base of Subsequent Taxes`. Then, drag and drop the "
"taxes in the :ref:`order they should be computed <taxes/base-subsequent>`."
msgstr ""
"Per calcolare un'imposta aggiuntiva in Odoo, :ref:`creare un'imposta <taxes/"
"configuration>`, inserire un nome per l'imposta, selezionare un "
":ref:`Calcolo imposta <taxes/configuration>`, impostare un "
":guilabel:`Importo`, e nella scheda :guilabel:`Opzioni avanzate`, abilitare "
":guilabel:`Influenza la base delle imposte successive`. Quindi, trascinare e "
"rilasciare le imposte nell':ref:`ordine in cui devono essere calcolate "
"<taxes/base-subsequent>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:466
msgid ""
"In Belgium, the formula to compute an environmental tax is: `(product price "
"+ environmental tax) x sales tax`. Therefore, our environmental tax has to "
"come *before* the sales tax in the computation sequence."
msgstr ""
"In Belgio, la formula per calcolare una tassa ambientale è: `(prezzo del "
"prodotto + imposta ambientale) x imposta sulle vendite`. Pertanto, la nostra "
"imposta ambientale deve venire *prima* dell'imposta sulle vendite nella "
"sequenza di calcolo."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:469
msgid ""
"In our case, we created a 5% environmental tax (Ecotax) and put it *before* "
"the Belgian base tax of 21%."
msgstr ""
"Nel nostro caso, abbiamo creato una tassa ambientale del 5% (Tassa "
"ambientale) e l'abbiamo anteposta all'imposta base belga del 21%."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:0
msgid "Environmental tax sequence in Belgium."
msgstr "Sequenza tassa ambientale in Belgio."

